1 (1) Coordinates with the office of rural development and other relevant state
2 agencies to align economic development funding streams and strategic initiatives.
3 (2) Strengthens alignment between workforce development programs and rural
4 employer needs.
5 (3) Identifies industry sectors and competitive advantages uniquely suited for rural
6 parishes.
7 (4) Provides periodic reporting to the Legislature regarding measurable outcomes,
8 benchmarks, and progress in advancing rural economic growth.
9 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Legislature of Louisiana hereby urges and
10 requests Louisiana Economic Development, consistent with its authority pursuant to R.S.
11 51:2301 to dedicate a staff person within the department to serve as a Rural Economic
12 Development Coordinator, whose responsibilities shall include implementing the directives
13 contained in this Resolution, facilitating interagency coordination related to rural economic
14 development initiatives, and tracking measurable outcomes in rural parishes.
15 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Legislature of Louisiana urges and requests
16 that all relevant state agencies cooperate with Louisiana Economic Development in carrying
17 out such coordinated efforts, consistent with existing statutory authority.
18 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that a copy of this Resolution be transmitted to the
19 secretary of Louisiana Economic Development, the commissioner of administration, and the
20 heads of each relevant state agencies, to include the Louisiana Department of Agriculture
21 and Forestry, the Louisiana Department of Conservation and Energy, the Louisiana
22 Department of Environmental Quality, the Louisiana Department of Health, the Louisiana
23 Department of Transportation and Development, Louisiana Economic Development,
24 Louisiana Works, the office of broadband development and connectivity, the office of
25 community development, and the office of rural development.
